#
# WHY toml IS THE 80TH RUST CLI LIBRARY
#
# toml-rs/toml is the canonical Rust TOML parser, used by Cargo
# itself and ~200,000 downstream Rust projects.  Distinct from
# every previously-documented Rust library in this taxonomy by
# being a TOML parser/serializer with serde integration.
#
# Five distinguishing characteristics:
#
#   1. CARGO ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — toml-rs parses every
#      Cargo.toml.  Every Rust project depends transitively on
#      toml-rs through cargo + cargo-* subcommands.
#
#   2. SERDE INTEGRATION — same #[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]
#      derive used for JSON / YAML / TOML / MessagePack / RON.
#      Distinct from format-specific TOML parsers in other
#      languages.
#
#   3. preserve_order FEATURE — opt-in flag for preserving key
#      insertion order during round-trip serialization.
#      Critical for editing Cargo.toml without reordering sections.
#
#   4. DATETIME FIRST-CLASS — TOML's distinctive feature
#      (offset-datetime, local-datetime, local-date, local-time)
#      parsed into toml::value::Datetime, separate from chrono.
#
#   5. ALEX-CRICHTON / TOML-RS ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — distinct
#      from David Tolnay (serde), Sean McArthur (Hyperium),
#      Sindre Sorhus (Node CLI), Vitaly Puzrin (nodeca).  Alex
#      Crichton is a Rust core team member + Cargo co-creator.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE lq CLI — clap derive + toml + serde-saphyr + jq subprocess
#
# lq's CLI is in lq.rs (single-file binary).  Uses clap v4
# derive with the Args struct.
#
# Flags:
#   --input {yaml|json|toml}    input format (auto-detect from
#                               file extension if absent;
#                               yaml default for stdin)
#   --output {yaml|jq|toml}     output format (default jq)
#   -y, --yaml-output           shortcut for --output yaml
#   -t, --toml-output           shortcut for --output toml
#   -T, --toml-input            shortcut for --input toml
#   -J, --json-input            shortcut for --input json
#   -i, --in-place              edit file in place
#   -s, --split QUERY           split output by per-document
#                               filename query
#   -c, --compact-output        jq -c (compact)
#   -r, --raw-output            jq -r (raw strings)
#   -j, --join-output           jq -j (no newlines)
#   -L PATH                     jq -L (module search dir)
#
# Positional arguments:
#   [JQ_QUERY]                  jq query (default ".")
#   [FILE]                      input file (default stdin)
#
# Standard:
#   -h, --help                  show help
#   -V, --version               show version
#
# Required external dependency: `jq` must be on PATH.  lq
# spawns `jq` as a subprocess to execute the query language.
#
# toml is used in lq.rs for parsing TOML inputs (via
# `--input toml` or .toml extension) and for emitting TOML
# outputs (via `--output toml` or `--toml-output` flag).
#
# Five-axis distinctness from all previously-documented Rust
# libraries:
#
#   1. TOML I/O ABSTRACTION — toml parses/emits TOML 1.0;
#      distinct from every other Axis.
#
#   2. SERDE FRAMEWORK INTEGRATION — same Rust structs work
#      across formats.
#
#   3. preserve_order ORDER PRESERVATION — opt-in for round-trip
#      editing.
#
#   4. DATETIME FIRST-CLASS — TOML's signature feature
#      preserved as toml::value::Datetime.
#
#   5. ALEX-CRICHTON / TOML-RS / CARGO ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE —
#      foundational to Rust packaging.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# COMMAND-LINE OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/clux/lq/blob/main/lq.rs
# clap v4 derive #[arg] + #[derive(Parser)] definitions.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

_arguments -s -S \
    '--input=[input format]:format:(yaml json toml)' \
    '--output=[output format]:format:(yaml jq toml)' \
    '(-y --yaml-output)'{-y,--yaml-output}'[shortcut: --output yaml]' \
    '(-t --toml-output)'{-t,--toml-output}'[shortcut: --output toml]' \
    '(-T --toml-input)'{-T,--toml-input}'[shortcut: --input toml]' \
    '(-J --json-input)'{-J,--json-input}'[shortcut: --input json]' \
    '(-i --in-place)'{-i,--in-place}'[edit input file in place]' \
    '(-s --split)'{-s+,--split=}'[per-document filename query]:query:_default' \
    '(-c --compact-output)'{-c,--compact-output}'[jq -c (compact output)]' \
    '(-r --raw-output)'{-r,--raw-output}'[jq -r (raw strings)]' \
    '(-j --join-output)'{-j,--join-output}'[jq -j (no newlines)]' \
    '-L+[jq module search directory]:directory:_files -/' \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    '1:jq query:_default' \
    '2:input file:_files -g "*.(yaml|yml|json|toml)"' \
    && ret=0

return ret
